178 as an annual contribution to the Alabama Transportation
179 Infrastructure Bank, if needed, for payment of debt service.
180 The Director of Transportation, with the consent of the
181 Governor and the Director of Finance, shall have the authority
182 to transfer any appropriation or any portion thereof between
183 and among subdivisions (a), (b) and (c) of this section
184 whenever such transfer shall be necessary to assure maximum
185 utilization of federal matching funds which shall become
186 available. In the event that there shall not be sufficient
187 funds available for payment of all appropriations hereinabove
188 made, the following provisions shall be applicable. In the
189 event of such insufficiency in respect of said revenues
190 accruing to the Department of Transportation: (1) the
191 appropriation made for Debt Service in subdivisions (a) and
192 (b) hereof shall be paid in full, and (2) the appropriations
193 from the revenues accruing to the Department of Transportation
194 that are herein made for the purposes referred to in
195 subdivisions (a), (b) and (c) except for Debt Service, hereof
196 shall be allocated among the purposes referred to in said
